## VII, 64. Expiation when one is defiled by a black bird of omen.

1\. What this black bird flying forth towards (me) has dropped here--may
the waters protect me from all that misfortune and evil!  
2. What this black bird has brushed here with thy mouth, O Nirtiti
(goddess of misfortune)-may Agni Gârhapatya (the god of the household
fire) free me from this sin!

